cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification and remote sensing. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The optimization of data tiling and structure of DCNN for multi-channel data and splicing edge effect suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of remote sensing data for land-use mapping suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
